message:
feat: add deterministic RNG seeding and runtime NeuroFlow configuration

Establishes deterministic simulation behavior via seeded RNG and adds runtime
configuration for NeuroFlow brain registration. Includes comprehensive test
coverage validating that identical seeds produce identical outcomes while
different seeds diverge as expected.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
DETERMINISM IMPROVEMENTS (crates/scriptbots-core/src/lib.rs)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TickSummary PartialEq (line 251):
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]  // Added PartialEq
pub struct TickSummary { ... }
```

Enables equality comparison for testing:
• Required for asserting history equality in determinism tests
• All fields are primitive types (copy semantics)
• Derived implementation compares all fields

Runtime NeuroFlow Toggle (lines 1090, 1125):
```rust
pub struct ScriptBotsConfig {
    // ... existing fields ...
    /// Enable registration of NeuroFlow-backed brains at runtime.
    pub enable_neuroflow_brain: bool,
}

impl Default for ScriptBotsConfig {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            // ... other defaults ...
            enable_neuroflow_brain: false,  // Disabled by default
        }
    }
}
```

Benefits:
• Decouples NeuroFlow from compile-time feature flags
• Users can enable/disable via configuration instead of rebuilding
• Supports A/B testing (run with/without NeuroFlow brains)
• Compatible with future dynamic brain loading

Determinism Test (lines 2477-2516):
```rust
fn run_seeded_history(mut config: ScriptBotsConfig, steps: usize) -> Vec<TickSummary> {
    config.history_capacity = steps;
    config.persistence_interval = 1;
    let mut world = WorldState::new(config).expect("world");
    for seed in 0..4 {
        world.spawn_agent(sample_agent(seed));
    }
    for _ in 0..steps {
        world.step();
    }
    world.history().cloned().collect()
}

#[test]
fn seeded_runs_are_deterministic() {
    const STEPS: usize = 48;
    let base_config = ScriptBotsConfig {
        world_width: 120,
        world_height: 120,
        food_cell_size: 20,
        initial_food: 0.3,
        food_respawn_interval: 2,
        food_respawn_amount: 0.25,
        food_max: 1.2,
        chart_flush_interval: 12,
        rng_seed: Some(1_234_567),
        ..ScriptBotsConfig::default()
    };

    // Same seed → same results
    let history_a = run_seeded_history(base_config.clone(), STEPS);
    let history_b = run_seeded_history(base_config.clone(), STEPS);
    assert_eq!(history_a, history_b, "seeded runs diverged");

    // Different seed → different results
    let mut different_seed = base_config;
    different_seed.rng_seed = Some(987654321);
    let history_c = run_seeded_history(different_seed, STEPS);
    assert_ne!(history_a, history_c, "different seeds should produce different histories");
}
```

Test validates:
• Reproducibility: Same seed + config → identical tick-by-tick history
• Sensitivity: Different seeds → divergent histories
• Coverage: 48 ticks, 4 agents, food respawn, all pipeline stages
• Comparison: 48 summaries × 7 fields = 336 data points

